President Barack Obama has proclaimed October 11, 2015, as International Day of the Girl. The proclamation highlights the importance of women and girls in our society and the need for their full participation in classrooms, workplaces, and communities. It emphasizes the progress made in promoting gender equality and the efforts to protect the rights of women and girls around the world. The proclamation also discusses the challenges faced by girls, such as lack of access to education and gender-based violence, and outlines initiatives, such as Let Girls Learn and the 1is2many campaign, aimed at addressing these challenges. The proclamation concludes by calling upon the people of the United States to observe the day with programs and activities that advance equality and opportunity for girls everywhere.